##"people in Wuhan want to taste, lest they cause trouble to others. "

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Deng Yafei, intern, Su Xiaoyu, reporter, thepaper.cn

"The man who borrowed the four batteries sent his own steamed bread, saying that he saw me admiring others' in the group, and that it was a perfect match for Sauerkraut and fish fillets. The fresh fish they had brought last time, and a big bag of their homemade nougat, which was creamy and not too sweet, and the crunchiness of the peanuts, which you could eat five or six in one sitting..."

Liu Hong, who lives in the Pearl District of Kaiping Li community in East West Lake District, Wuhan, reads the daily notes of her neighbors on Wechat and remembers a few heartwarming things that have just happened between her and her neighbors.

"The people of Wuhan are actually quite lovely. They are straightforward and have the spirit of the rivers and lakes. They are very helpful and warm-hearted. But the people of Wuhan also love face-saving. They want to taste, for fear of causing trouble to others! " Liu Hong told the paper's www.thepaper.cn  several stories about neighbors helping each other and being polite to each other.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Staff braved the rain to hand out group-order meat to residents. All images in this article are provided by the interviewees

A bag of family-sized care dishes

One of Liu Hong's neighbors, Li Ping (not his real name) , had a kidney transplant two years ago and had another rejection at the end of 2019. Before the New Year, Li Ping's lover went home to visit his family. Unexpectedly, the city was sealed off and the couple was forced to separate.

Community after the implementation of closed management, he had to go outside the community to get living materials, but his home lives on the 7th floor, up and down the stairs is really too much.

Worried about her husband infection but in another place, Li Ping's wife worried, "my husband is susceptible to the crowd, usually even cold are strictly guarded, epidemic situation is even more difficult. "

Knowing this, Liu Hong reached out to his neighbor and rounded up a generous helping of heart food that he could eat for at least two weeks.

What's in this bag of Coleslaw? It was a hard morning for Liu Hong's daughter to buy vegetables (cabbages, carrots, green peppers, cucumbers, green beans, etc.) from her home on the streets of Fufu, Fufu from her community volunteers, 30 eggs from Fufu, from her grandfather who lives below the House of Liu Hong.

When collecting the 30 eggs, the grandfather refused to accept Liu Hong's money, saying, "help the neighbors do not charge, " but Liu Hong insisted on giving him.

After collecting the care package, the community volunteer Chen Qiongfang volunteered to deliver the food in the group. Chen Qiongfang carried the 20-odd catties of vegetables and fruits to the seventh floor, the Gasp.

Li Ping's wife said her husband was shocked when he saw Chen carry such a heavy dish up the stairs in one breath. "I'm not weaker than a young man, " she said at the time. "Now you have more food at home, I feel at ease. "

In addition to heart-warming vegetables, Li was helped by volunteer teams organized by the community during the outbreak.

During the outbreak, he had to go to the hospital for regular checks, and a volunteer with a pass picked him up at his home to go to the hospital and pick him up when he was done.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Property owners over the age of 60 are given free cabbage from one building to another.

"people in Wuhan want to taste, lest they cause trouble to others. "

Below Liu Hong lives an old teacher, in his seventies, who lives with his wife.

"older people, who don't know anything about smartphone software, only learn to use their smartphones to make calls and transfer money through wechat under the repeated guidance of others, " Liu Hong said, "But during the outbreak, people had to use software or wechat group chat to order supplies, and the old man was stumped by what seemed to be the simplest operation. "

After the implementation of closed management of the community, Liu Hong every time online shopping some materials, but also by the way ask what the old master needs.

Once, the old man wanted to buy salt, noodles, soap, and disinfectant, but the community was forced to buy food, and Liu Hong, who happened to have some at home, packed up his own soap and disinfectant and gave it to the old man.

When the old man offered to pay Liu Hong Money, she quickly refused: "Oh, I just want to do good, not into selling things SA. "

Even so, the old man insisted on paying, not only to give, but to give more every time. Once, when Liu Hong bought something for $206, the old man asked Liu Hong to give him $230. Liu Hong refused to accept, wechat transfer was returned, the old man again transfer.

Come and go, Liu Hong "surrender" , she smiled and the old man and discussed: "Well, we meet halfway, you give me 210 yuan, 230 yuan I will never accept. You also peace of mind, I also peace of mind. " Finally and the old man reached an agreement.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Neighbors Record daily activities of mutual help on Wechat.

Liu Hong also heard that a community volunteer, Liu Jingqian, helped deliver food to a woman who was home alone with her child. The woman's husband had gone to work outside the city, and then came across the city of Wuhan, has not been able to go home for more than 40 days, Liu Jingqian know she a person to take care of the children is not convenient to go downstairs to get supplies, each time enthusiastically to send supplies to her door.

The woman did not know how to thank Liu Jingqian, so she set aside some of her supplies and put them at the door of Liu Jingqian's house not far away. Liu Jingqian home to see, and then sent back, two people pushed several times. "I don't think this dish will be taken in if it is put out of order, " joked Liu

In Liu Hong's words, this is how people in Wuhan look on a daily basis. "This is how people in Wuhan are, they love face, they want flavor, they like to be polite, they don't want to cause trouble to others, but it's what neighbors do to help each other out. "
